"You must guess what it is. The {g|LanternKing}Lantern King{/g} loves masks. Since ancient times he's wandered the planes, assuming the forms of the most unique and unusual creatures. But his own masks are something more. Each of them holds a fraction of his essence."
{n}Magdh's voice becomes dull, as if she is sinking into memory.{/n}
"He made this mask long ago, when he was young, as was all {g|First World}the First World{/g}. And, as with many early creations, its author disapproved of it. It betrayed too much compassion, a quality that annoyed the young demigod."
